<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-09T23:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-09T23:29:00-05:00" n="528" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d528">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1301</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-09T23:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1917—11 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>General Delgado, a congressman, with four other important rebel chiefs,
                            and 400 men surrendered to Government at Arroyo Blanco, Camaguey
                            Province today. Some soldiers who deserted at Camaguey at inception
                            revolt are among these men. Surrender regarded as most important by the
                            Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>